    "introduction": "Nora Rios was born and raised in Stockholm, Sweden. She began her acting career in an early age staring in Swedish television shows such as Bankrånet (2013) & Arkeologens dotter (2018). Nora began her professional acting career by appearing in Swedish short films and television series, and first gained recognition for her role as Sulle in Caliphate (2020). Since then she has gone on to star as the lead actress of the Swedish TV show Heartbeats (2022) resulting in Nora being nominated for Actress of the year in the official Swedish television award Kristallen. Nora was also nominated as rising star at the annual Stockholm Film Festival 2020.",
